  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Operational Capacities of Gambian Authorities to Manage Borders</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to contribute to enhancing operational capacity of the Government of The Gambia to manage borders. The proposed project will address the aforementioned concerns through an integrated three-pillar outcome approach:  1) Improved physical infrastructure, including facilities and equipment, at border posts for effective border management; 2) Strengthened migration data collection and analysis through expansion of the Border Management Information Systems under deployment; and 3) Enhanced institutional capacity through the promotion of inter-agency cooperation to address immigration related risks and through the social mobilization of communities to ensure peaceful co-existence for economic development.</narrative>
  </description>
